Title: Alton Downs Gravity (P196240), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Alton Downs Gravity (P196240) contains a total of 3868 point data values acquired at a spacing between 804 and 6436 metres. The data is located in QLD, SA and were acquired in 1962, under project No. 196240 for Delhi Petroleum Pty Ltd.

Lineage: This Alton Downs Gravity (P196240), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Alton Downs Gravity (P196240) survey acquired for Delhi Petroleum Pty Ltd. This dataset contains a total of 3868 point data values. The data is located in QLD, SA and were acquired in 1962. The point located data were collected in irregular layout at a station spacing between 804 and 6436 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.
SourceDescription: This Alton Downs Gravity (P196240), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Alton Downs Gravity (P196240) survey acquired for Delhi Petroleum Pty Ltd.

Lineage: This Canegrass, Monash, Upper Murray Basin Detailed Gravity (P196380), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Canegrass, Monash, Upper Murray Basin Detailed Gravity (P196380) survey acquired for Department of Mines and Energy South Australia (SADME). This dataset contains a total of 180 point data values. The data is located in SA and were acquired in 1963. Title: Lake Betty Gravity (P196366), gravity point data

The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Lake Betty Gravity (P196366) contains a total of 1468 point data values acquired at a spacing of 804 metres. The data is located in WA and were acquired in 1963, under project No. 196366 for West Australian Petroleum Pty Ltd.

Lineage: This Missionary Plains Gravity (P196131), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Missionary Plains Gravity (P196131) survey acquired for Magellan Petroleum Australia Ltd. This dataset contains a total of 1248 point data values. The data is located in NT and were acquired in 1960. The point located data were collected in grid layout at an average station spacing of 804 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.
